sentences.english: The ball couldn't recognize the top because he looked so different than before.
sentences.chinese: 陀螺看上去跟以前迥然不同，球都认不出他来了。

sentences.english: The rational FEM formulation, which is quite different from the usual FEM formulation, is proposed here.
sentences.chinese: 提出了与常现有限元迥然不同的理性有限元列式。

sentences.english: The morphology and culture characters of the pathogen are different from those of H. maydis.
sentences.chinese: 从病斑形态和培养性状与小斑病菌迥然不同。

sentences.english: This is much different from learning a new behavior.
sentences.chinese: 这同学会一个新习惯迥然不同。

sentences.english: Me and Richard create similar music but we're very different people.
sentences.chinese: 我和理查德创造出的音乐相似但是我俩性格迥然不同。

sentences.english: But the reasons for this differ.
The hydrogeological parameter characteristics in salt-lake area are different apparently from that in fresh-water area.
sentences.chinese: 益湖区的水文地质参数特性与淡水区迥然不同。

sentences.english: Opinions concerning strict parental discipline vary widely.
sentences.chinese: 针对峻厉的家教的观点迥然不同。

sentences.english: My method for studying English differs from yours completely.
sentences.chinese: 我学习英语的方法和你的方法迥然不同。

sentences.english: The attitude of the professional thief is quite different.
sentences.chinese: 惯偷的态度则迥然不同。

sentences.english: They assume strength, not fragility, and as a result they behave very differently.
sentences.chinese: 他们强调坚强，不脆弱，结果孩子们的表现迥然不同。

sentences.english: Life on a farm is a far cry from what I've been used to.
sentences.chinese: 农场生活与我已过惯的日子迥然不同。

sentences.english: We were as different as the Louvre and Madison Square Garden.
sentences.chinese: 我们就像卢浮宫和麦迪逊加登广场一样迥然不同。

sentences.english: Men and women have very different views on haircuts.
sentences.chinese: 男人和女人对理发的看法迥然不同。

sentences.english: Although they were both New Englanders, their writerly temperaments were quite different.
sentences.chinese: 虽然都来自新英格兰，两人的文字性情却迥然不同。

definition: entirely different/different as black and white
not at all the same/substantially different
as different as can be (idiom)/poles apart
lit. as different as sky and earth (idiom)/fig. night and day difference/opposite extremes/a world of difference/a far cry from
to be precisely the same/to be no different
as different as heaven and earth (idiom)/worlds apart
there cannot be another one like it
to have nothing in common with each other (idiom)
